# Memory Bank Protocol

Persistent context across sessions. Read on boot, update after work.

## Boot (Session Start)

Read in order:
1. `projectbrief.md` — What is SF-Bench
2. `productContext.md` — Why it exists
3. `systemPatterns.md` — How it's built
4. `techContext.md` — Technology stack
5. `activeContext.md` — Current focus
6. `progress.md` — Status

## Update (After Work)

### Update `activeContext.md` when:
- Starting new work → Update "Current Focus"
- Completing work → Add to "Recent Changes"
- Hitting blockers → Add to "Blockers"

### Update `progress.md` when:
- Feature completed → Move to "Completed"
- New todo identified → Add to "Todos"
- Issue found → Add to "Known Issues"

## Format

### Recent Changes Entry
```
- [YYYY-MM-DD] Brief description
```

### Todo Entry
```
- [ ] Task description - [Priority: High/Medium/Low]
```

## Don't Over-Update

Update only on meaningful changes:
- ✅ Feature completed
- ✅ Significant refactoring
- ✅ New blocker or resolution
- ❌ Minor formatting fixes
- ❌ Small bug fixes
- ❌ Documentation tweaks
